reviewText: HI All,  I used to watch "Trackdown" when the series was run some years back & enjoyed it very much for a 1/2 hr. episode. Used to wish it was an hour. This DVD is great. there are a few minor glitches, but it is from an old source so was not really disappointed. For people like me that like the old series westerns I think would like it. This one is noted as volume #1, so if & when volume #2 comes out I would like to have it also, along with any future releases that might be put out. RLW.

reviewText: Young Robert Culp is our hero Texas Ranger Hoby Gillman in this 30 minute relatively routine western for it's day. Stories are generally pretty interesting but quality of picture detracts substantially. Not near the released video quality of Wanted Dead or Alive, the Steve McQueen oater that sprang form this very series. But then Robert Culp was no Steve McQueen so I'm sure didn't rate the post production effort to produce watchable discs. This show lasted two seasons which is indicative of the routine story lines and original production values, I'd judge. Of interest to die hard western (like me) fans principally. Too bad about the image quality, really.
summary: pretty good show - lousy video quality
